children.subject: ok, I found out the answer to my question - looking at last year's CS61B itinerary, it looks like signups happened the Friday before classes started.  Also, people on waitlist were allowed to sign up for labs and discussions.  So I'm good on both fronts, assuming I get off of waitlist.

history.content:
so I sort of got screwed by the enrollment policies, though it's my fault since I probably should have read the fine print more carefully.  I declared for CS after Spring, but wanted to take 61B in the fall since many people who took Data Structures in CC seemed to do this.  So I thought I would simply be able to Phase 2 this class since I thought I had priority.  Nope, apparently lost priority for this one and only one class by declaring (too soon).  Not only that, but I get no priority on the waitlist, so I'm buried with a big number.

Anyhow, just wondering if anyone knows when the signups for discussions and labs generally have been in the past for Hilfinger?  I'm reasonably sure the class will expand such that everyone off of waitlist will get in.  However, worried that I'll get leftovers for lab times, especially if the signup date is before I get enrolled for the class.  (Professor Wagner actually had a signup in the middle of July last year for his Data 8 class).
history.subject: 61B expansion and lab/disc signup date
